# Development Standards and Best Practices

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Prefer functional components in React with hooks
- Use camelCase for JavaScript/TypeScript variables and functions
- Use snake_case for database columns and API endpoints
- Use PascalCase for React components and interfaces
- Use kebab-case for file names and URLs

## Architecture Patterns
- Follow the repository pattern for data access
- Keep business logic in service layers
- Use Supabase client for all database operations
- Implement proper error handling with toast notifications
- Use real-time subscriptions for live data updates
- Follow RESTful API conventions for Edge Functions

## Component Guidelines
- Create reusable UI components in `/components/ui/`
- Implement proper TypeScript interfaces for all props
- Use consistent naming: `ComponentName.tsx` for components
- Export components as default exports
- Use proper imports from `lucide-react` (verify icon names exist)
- Implement loading states and error boundaries

## Database Standards
- Use Supabase migrations for all schema changes
- Implement Row Level Security (RLS) policies
- Use proper indexing for performance
- Store file uploads in Supabase Storage
- Use JSONB for flexible data structures (preferences, metadata)
- Follow naming conventions: `table_name`, `column_name`

## Authentication & Authorization
- Use Supabase Auth for user management
- Implement role-based access control (RBAC)
- Protect routes with `SimpleProtectedRoute`
- Validate user roles in Edge Functions
- Store user profiles in `public.users` table

## Real-time Features
- Use `useRealtimeSubscription` hook for live updates
- Implement proper cleanup in useEffect
- Handle connection states gracefully
- Use optimistic updates where appropriate

## Error Handling
- Use `toast` from `sonner` for user notifications
- Implement proper try-catch blocks
- Log errors appropriately
- Provide meaningful error messages to users
- Handle network failures gracefully

## Testing & Quality
- Run `read_lints` after making changes
- Test Edge Functions locally before deployment
- Verify all imports and exports
- Check for TypeScript errors
- Ensure responsive design on mobile devices

## Deployment
- Use `npx supabase db push` for database changes
- Deploy Edge Functions with `supabase functions deploy`
- Only deploy to Vercel when explicitly requested
- Test functionality in development before production